title: You are an intervert
details: In general terms, introverts are people who prefer to think more than talk. They need to spend time alone, do not seek out loud social gatherings, and usually feel guilty about their less friendly nature

title: You are an extrovert
details: Extroverts are often described as happy, positive, cheerful, and sociable. They aren't as likely to dwell on problems or ponder difficulties. While they experience difficulties and troubles like anyone else, extroverts are often more able to let it roll off their backs.
